quran[49]{c,v,t}:
  50,27,"His [devil] companion will say, “Our Lord, I did not mislead him, but he himself was far astray.”"
  50,28,"Allah will say, “Do not argue in My presence, for I had already given you the warning"
  50,29,"My Word cannot be changed, nor am I unjust to My slaves.”"
  50,30,"[Beware of] the Day when We will say to Hell, “Have you reached your fill?” It will say, “Are there any more?”"
  50,31,"Paradise will be brought near to the righteous, not far off"
  50,32,"[It will be said], “This is what you were promised; this is for everyone who constantly turned [to Allah] and was dutiful"
  50,33,"who feared the Most Compassionate unseen, and came with a devoted heart"
  50,34,Enter it in peace. This is the Day of eternity.”
  50,35,"They will have therein all what they wish for, and We have yet more"
  50,36,"How many nations We destroyed before them [Makkans] who were stronger than them in might! They traveled through the land. Did they find any escape"
  50,37,"Indeed, in that is a reminder for anyone who has a [mindful] heart or lends an attentive ear"
  50,38,"Indeed, We created the heavens and earth and all that is between them in six days, and no weariness touched Us"
  50,39,"So bear patiently [O Prophet] what they say, and glorify the praise of your Lord before sunrise and before sunset"
  50,40,And glorify Him in the night and after the prayers
  50,41,And listen! On the Day when the Caller will call out from a nearby place
  50,42,"the Day when they will hear the Blast [of the second Trumpet] in truth. That is the Day of resurrection"
  50,43,"Indeed, it is We Who give life and cause death, and to Us is the final return"
  50,44,"On the Day when the earth will be rent asunder for them as they hasten forth [from their graves]. That is an easy gathering for Us"
  50,45,"We know best what they say, and you are not there to compel them to believe. But remind with the Qur’an those who fear My warning"
  51,1,"By the winds that scatters [dust]"
  51,2,and by the heavily-laden clouds with water
  51,3,and by the ships that sail with ease
  51,4,"and by the angels who distribute [blessings] by His command"
  51,5,"Indeed, what you are promised is true"
  51,6,and the Judgment will surely come to pass
  51,7,By the heaven with its pathways
  51,8,"Indeed, you [Makkans] have conflicting views [about the truth]"
  51,9,He who is diverted from it is destined to be diverted
  51,10,Doomed are those who base their beliefs on conjecture
  51,11,those who are steeped in ignorance heedlessly
  51,12,"They ask [mockingly], “When is the Day of Judgment?”"
  51,13,It is the Day when they will be punished by the Fire
  51,14,"[It will be said], “Taste your punishment! This is what you were seeking to hasten.”"
  51,15,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and springs"
  51,16,"receiving what their Lord will give them, for they were indeed doers of good beforehand"
  51,17,They used to sleep but little at night
  51,18,and before dawn they would seek forgiveness
  51,19,"and in their wealth, there was a share for the beggar and the destitute"
  51,20,On earth there are signs for those who are certain in faith
  51,21,and also in your own selves. Do you not see
  51,22,And in the heaven is your provision and all that you are promised
  51,23,"By the Lord of the heaven and earth, this [resurrection] is certainly as true as the fact that you can speak"
  51,24,Has there come to you the story of Abraham’s honored guests
  51,25,"When they came to him and said, “Peace.” He said, “Upon you be peace.” [saying to himself] “Unknown people!”"
  51,26,"Then he went quickly to his household, and came with a fat [roasted] calf"
  51,27,"and placed it before them and said, “Will you not eat?”"
  51,28,"He perceived a fear of them. They said, “Do not be afraid,” and gave him glad tidings of a knowledgeable son"
  51,29,"His wife cried out loud, and struck her face [in astonishment] and said, “[I am] a barren old woman!”"
  51,30,"They said, “This is what your Lord said. Indeed, He is the All-Wise, the All-Knowing.”"